"what is anthropology anthropology is the study of man of all time and space it has four branches physical anthropology sociocultural anthropology archaeological anthropology and linguistic anthropology physical anthropology studies human as biological organisms and tries to differentiate human from other species physical anthropologists study the human origin Evolution and their physical attributes social anthropology studies the ways in which people live in different social and cultural settings across the globe archaeological anthropology examines people and cultures of the past and last but not least linguistic anthropology studies the nature of human languages in context of those cultures that develop them "